Pitkin first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusLA>{{Cite web|title= 2010 Census of Population - Population and Housing Unit Counts - Louisiana |url=https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/2010/cph-2/cph-2-20.pdf|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402175429/https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/2010/cph-2/cph-2-20.pdf| archive-date=April 2, 2024}}</ref> '

According to the 2010 census, of its 576 population who live in 230 households, their median age was 41.6, 541 are [[White American|White]], 10 are [[Multiracial American|multiracial]], 3 are [[Asian American|Asian]], 2 are some other [[Race in the United States|race]], 1 is [[African American]]; 10 have [[Hispanic and Latino American|Latino ethnicity]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=2010 |work=[[United States Census Bureau]] |publisher=United States Department of Commerce |accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref>

